---
// The landing page — trimmed to a punchy first impression.
//
// Sections kept:
//   1. Hero (with the gradle snippet + the four-tile feature grid)
//   2. Marquee strip
//   3. The dual-write trap (visual diagram, with link into /concepts/)
//   4. "Three doors" CTA → Concepts | Learn | Reference + final big CTA
//
// Sections that USED to live here and now live deeper:
//   - Five primitives  →  to be ported to /concepts/the-five-primitives/
//   - Wallet two-phases  →  to be ported to /learn/your-first-action/
//   - Capabilities grid  →  represented in /reference/ via the entry list
//   - Install snippets  →  /learn/getting-started/ with full StackPicker
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../components/CodeBlock.astro";

// Deployment base path (trailing slash already baked in by Astro).
// Lets the hardcoded internal hrefs below survive a move to a subpath deploy
// (e.g. GitHub Pages `/ekbatan/`) without source edits.
const B = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Ekbatan — Outbox-native Java persistence">
<section id="top" class="border-b-2 border-ink"><div class="container-px max-w-7xl mx-auto" style="padding-top:10rem;padding-bottom:6rem;min-height:calc(100vh - 4rem)"><div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap justify-center items-stretch gap-10"><h1 class="font-display font-bold text-balance hero-h1">Ekbatan<br><span class="bg-orange text-paper px-3 -mx-1 inline-block">event-driven</span><br><span class="italic">java</span><br><span class="font-normal">persistence</span><br>framework<span class="text-orange">.</span></h1><div class="flex flex-col gap-6 max-w-md justify-between"><div style="align-self:flex-start;margin-top:1.4rem" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 brut-border bg-yellow px-3 py-1.5 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-ink rounded-full blink"></span>v0.0.3 · Apache 2.0 · Java 25+</div><p class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">Ekbatan is a Java persistence framework that writes your domain state and the matching events <span class="bg-yellow px-1">in one atomic transaction</span>. No dual writes. No drift. The database is the single source of truth — for both.</p><p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">A replacement for Hibernate, Spring Data, or hand-rolled JDBC. Drops into Spring Boot, Quarkus, or Micronaut — doesn't replace them.</p><div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4"><a href={`${B}learn/getting-started/`} class="brut-border brut-shadow bg-orange text-paper font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-widest px-6 py-3.5 hover:translate-x-1 hover:translate-y-1 hover:shadow-none transition-all">Get started →</a><a href="https://github.com/zyraz-io/ekbatan" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="brut-border brut-shadow bg-paper font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-widest px-6 py-3.5 inline-flex items-center gap-2 hover:translate-x-1 hover:translate-y-1 hover:shadow-none transition-all"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 .5C5.65.5.5 5.65.5 12c0 5.08 3.29 9.39 7.86 10.91.58.11.79-.25.79-.56v-2c-3.2.7-3.88-1.36-3.88-1.36-.52-1.32-1.27-1.67-1.27-1.67-1.04-.71.08-.7.08-.7 1.15.08 1.76 1.18 1.76 1.18 1.02 1.75 2.69 1.25 3.34.96.1-.74.4-1.25.72-1.54-2.55-.29-5.24-1.28-5.24-5.69 0-1.26.45-2.29 1.18-3.1-.12-.29-.51-1.46.11-3.04 0 0 .97-.31 3.18 1.18.92-.26 1.91-.39 2.9-.39.99 0 1.98.13 2.9.39 2.21-1.49 3.18-1.18 3.18-1.18.62 1.58.23 2.75.11 3.04.74.81 1.18 1.84 1.18 3.1 0 4.42-2.7 5.4-5.27 5.68.41.36.78 1.07.78 2.16v3.2c0 .31.21.68.79.56C20.21 21.39 23.5 17.08 23.5 12 23.5 5.65 18.35.5 12 .5z"></path></svg> Star on GitHub</a></div></div></div></div></section><section id="problem" class="border-b-2 border-ink"><div class="container-px max-w-7xl mx-auto py-20 md:py-28"><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 brut-border bg-ink text-paper font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest px-3 py-1.5"><span class="text-yellow">01</span><span>/</span><span>The dual-write trap</span></div><h2 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tight max-w-4xl text-balance mt-6 leading-[0.95]">Two writes. Two systems. <span class="bg-orange text-paper px-2 inline-block">One silent drift.</span></h2><p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed">Every business change produces two things at once — a new state, and an event that records how it got there. Persisting them as separate writes is where systems start to drift out of sync.</p><div class="mt-14 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8"><div class="brut-border brut-shadow-orange bg-paper flex flex-col"><div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b-2 border-ink px-5 py-3 bg-ink text-paper"><h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">Two writes</h3><span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1 bg-orange text-paper">✗ broken</span></div><div class="p-8 min-h-[280px] flex flex-col items-center justify-center flex-1"><svg class="diagram diagram-broken" viewBox="-10 0 340 260" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" aria-label="Two writes: the app pushes state to DB and events to Kafka as separate writes. One signal arrives; the other fizzles mid-flight — the broken dual-write pattern."><line x1="160" y1="55" x2="50" y2="200" class="wire"></line><line x1="160" y1="55" x2="270" y2="200" class="wire"></line><rect x="-10" y="-1.5" width="20" height="3" class="signal"><animateMotion dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite" rotate="auto" keyTimes="0; 0.33; 1" keyPoints="0; 1; 1" calcMode="linear" path="M 160 55 L 50 200"></animateMotion><animate attributeName="opacity" values="1;1;0;0" keyTimes="0;0.32;0.33;1" dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite"></animate></rect><g><animateMotion dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite" rotate="auto" keyTimes="0; 0.33; 0.72; 1" keyPoints="0; 0; 0.75; 0.75" calcMode="linear" path="M 160 55 L 270 200"></animateMotion><path d="M -10 0 L -8.33 0 L -6.67 0 L -5 0 L -3.33 0 L -1.67 0 L 0 0 L 1.67 0 L 3.33 0 L 5 0 L 6.67 0 L 8.33 0 L 10 0" class="signal signal-fail" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="butt" fill="none"><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;0;1;1;0" keyTimes="0;0.32;0.33;0.99;1" dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite"></animate></path></g><g class="box"><rect x="115" y="15" width="90" height="40"></rect><text x="160" y="35">APP</text></g><g class="box"><rect x="10" y="200" width="80" height="40"></rect><text x="50" y="220">DB</text></g><g class="box"><rect x="230" y="200" width="80" height="40"></rect><text x="270" y="220">KAFKA</text></g><text x="50" y="254" class="label label-ok">STATE SAVED</text><text x="270" y="254" class="label label-fail">PUBLISH FAILED</text></svg></div><p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest border-t-2 border-ink px-5 py-3 bg-muted">Crash between writes ⇒ DB and Kafka disagree.</p></div><div class="brut-border brut-shadow-yellow bg-paper flex flex-col"><div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b-2 border-ink px-5 py-3 bg-ink text-paper"><h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">One write + outbox</h3><span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1 bg-yellow text-ink">✓ Ekbatan</span></div><div class="p-8 space-y-4 min-h-[280px] flex flex-col justify-center text-center flex-1"><div class="mx-auto inline-flex font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest brut-border bg-paper px-5 py-2.5 flow-box">app</div><svg class="flow-wire" viewBox="-10 0 50 70" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="15" y1="0" x2="15" y2="70" class="wire"/><rect x="-10" y="-1.5" width="20" height="3" class="signal"><animateMotion dur="2s" repeatCount="indefinite" rotate="auto" keyTimes="0; 0.5; 1" keyPoints="0; 1; 1" calcMode="linear" path="M 15 -10 L 15 80"/></rect></svg><div class="brut-border bg-yellow p-3 flow-box"><div class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-center mb-2">database (one tx)</div><div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 font-mono text-xs"><div class="brut-border bg-paper py-2 text-center">state</div><div class="brut-border bg-paper py-2 text-center">outbox</div></div></div><svg class="flow-wire" viewBox="-10 0 50 70" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="15" y1="0" x2="15" y2="70" class="wire"/><rect x="-10" y="-1.5" width="20" height="3" class="signal"><animateMotion dur="2s" repeatCount="indefinite" rotate="auto" keyTimes="0; 0.5; 1" keyPoints="0; 0; 1" calcMode="linear" path="M 15 -10 L 15 80"/></rect></svg><div class="mx-auto inline-flex font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest brut-border bg-paper px-5 py-2.5 flow-box">Kafka</div></div><p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest border-t-2 border-ink px-5 py-3 bg-muted">CDC tails the outbox — events ship later, always in sync.</p></div></div><div class="mt-10 text-center"><a href={`${B}concepts/the-dual-write-trap/`} class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest brut-border bg-paper hover:bg-yellow transition-colors px-5 py-3 inline-flex items-center gap-2">Read the full explanation →</a></div></div></section><section class="border-b-2 border-ink"><div class="container-px max-w-7xl mx-auto" style="padding-top:6rem;padding-bottom:6rem"><div class="flex flex-col" style="gap:5.5rem"><div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] gap-8 items-start"><div><div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3"><div class="inline-flex items-center brut-border bg-muted text-ink font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1">learn by example</div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 brut-border bg-ink text-paper font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1"><span class="text-yellow">01</span><span>/</span><span>Model</span></div></div><h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mt-5 leading-tight">MODEL is Immutable. Attaches its own events upon change.</h3><p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">A domain object that emits events when it mutates. <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">deposit(amount)</code> returns a new <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">Wallet</code> with a <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">WalletMoneyDepositedEvent</code> attached inside the same builder call. State and event coupled at the source — never two writes. Don't need events for a table? Extend <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">Entity</code> instead — same persistence surface, no event emission.</p></div><CodeBlock filename="Wallet.java" language="java" shadow="yellow" code={`@AutoBuilder
public final class Wallet extends Model<Wallet, …> {
  public final BigDecimal balance;
  // …

  public Wallet deposit(BigDecimal amount) {
    return copy()
      .withEvent(new WalletMoneyDepositedEvent(id, amount))
      .balance(balance.add(amount))
      .build();
  }
}`} /></div><div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] gap-8 items-start"><div><div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3"><div class="inline-flex items-center brut-border bg-muted text-ink font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1">learn by example</div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 brut-border bg-ink text-paper font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1"><span class="text-yellow">02</span><span>/</span><span>Action</span></div></div><h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mt-5 leading-tight">ACTION Reads, mutates, PLAN the changes. ActionExecutor will persist the PLANNED changes.</h3><p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">A unit of business work. <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">perform()</code> reads from a repository, mutates the model, stages the new version on <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">plan()</code>. No transaction handling, no direct writes. Once <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">perform()</code> returns, <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">ActionExecutor</code> opens one database transaction and persists everything atomically — domain rows AND the matching events in the outbox table. All of it commits, or all of it rolls back.</p></div><CodeBlock filename="WalletDepositAction.java" language="java" shadow="orange" code={`@EkbatanAction
public class WalletDepositAction extends Action<Params, Wallet> {

  protected Wallet perform(Principal p, Params params) {
    var wallet = walletRepository.getById(params.walletId());
    return plan().update(wallet.deposit(params.amount()));
  }
  // …
}`} /></div><div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] gap-8 items-start"><div><div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3"><div class="inline-flex items-center brut-border bg-muted text-ink font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1">learn by example</div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 brut-border bg-ink text-paper font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1"><span class="text-yellow">03</span><span>/</span><span>Action Executor</span></div></div><h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mt-5 leading-tight">ACTION EXECUTOR runs the action. Wherever you call it from.</h3><p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">The framework's single entry point. Inject it via DI and call <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">execute(SomeAction.class, params)</code> from anywhere — a Spring <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">@RestController</code> (shown), a Quarkus resource, a scheduled job, a CLI command. The executor handles discovery, <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">perform()</code>, the transaction, and the atomic commit.</p></div><CodeBlock filename="WalletController.java" language="java" shadow="yellow" code={`@RestController
@RequestMapping("/wallets")
public class WalletController {

  private final ActionExecutor executor;
  // …

  @PostMapping("/{id}/deposit")
  public Wallet deposit(@PathVariable UUID id, @RequestBody Body body) throws Exception {
    return executor.execute(() -> "rest-user", WalletDepositAction.class,
        new Params(Id.of(Wallet.class, id), body.amount()));
  }
}`} /></div><div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] gap-8 items-start"><div><div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3"><div class="inline-flex items-center brut-border bg-muted text-ink font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1">learn by example</div><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 brut-border bg-ink text-paper font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest px-2 py-1"><span class="text-yellow">04</span><span>/</span><span>Repository</span></div></div><h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mt-5 leading-tight">jOOQ-backed. Thin extension.</h3><p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">A short subclass of <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">ModelRepository</code>. Inherits <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">getById</code> / <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">add</code> / <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-yellow px-1">update</code>; custom queries written in the typed jOOQ DSL when you need them — no JPA, no annotations soup.</p></div><CodeBlock filename="WalletRepository.java" language="java" shadow="default" code={`@EkbatanRepository
public class WalletRepository extends ModelRepository<Wallet, …> {

  public List<Wallet> findAllByOwnerId(UUID ownerId) {
    return readonlyDb()
      .selectFrom(WALLETS)
      .where(WALLETS.OWNER_ID.eq(ownerId))
      .fetch(this::fromRecord);
  }
  // …
}`} /></div></div>
</div></section><div class="bg-yellow border-b-2 border-ink overflow-hidden py-5"><div class="flex marquee-track w-max"><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center gap-10 px-5"><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">ATOMIC</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">OUTBOX-NATIVE</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">JAVA 25</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">JOOQ</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">VIRTUAL THREADS</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">MULTI-DATABASE</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">SHARDED</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">SPRING · QUARKUS · MICRONAUT · PLAIN JAVA</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">POSTGRES · MARIADB · MYSQL</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span></div><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center gap-10 px-5"><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">ATOMIC</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">OUTBOX-NATIVE</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">JAVA 25</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">JOOQ</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">VIRTUAL THREADS</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">MULTI-DATABASE</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">SHARDED</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">SPRING · QUARKUS · MICRONAUT · PLAIN JAVA</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold ">POSTGRES · MARIADB · MYSQL</span><span class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-orange">★</span></div></div></div>
<section class="border-b-2 border-ink">
  <div class="container-px max-w-7xl mx-auto py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 brut-border bg-ink text-paper font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest px-3 py-1.5"><span class="text-yellow">→</span><span>Where to next</span></div>
    <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tight max-w-4xl text-balance mt-6 leading-[0.95]">Three doors. <span class="bg-yellow px-2">Pick yours.</span></h2>
    <div class="mt-14 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
      <a href={`${B}concepts/`} class="brut-border brut-shadow-orange bg-paper p-8 flex flex-col gap-4 hover:-translate-x-1 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-none transition-all min-h-[280px]">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">01 · why</span>
          <span class="font-mono text-xl">→</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Concepts</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed flex-1">The model the framework rests on. Dual-write, outbox-by-construction, the two-phase action lifecycle, sharding theory. Read once and the rest reads like notation.</p>
        <div class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest mt-auto">Start with the dual-write trap →</div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${B}learn/`} class="brut-border brut-shadow-yellow bg-paper p-8 flex flex-col gap-4 hover:-translate-x-1 hover:-translate-y-1 hover:shadow-none transition-all min-h-[280px]">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
